---
import imgAtom from "../../public/atom.svg";
---
<site-section>
    <site-title>
        <h1>The Atomico Ecosystem</h1>
    </site-title>
    <site-text>
        Atomico has a modular development ecosystem that involves packaging, <strong>state management</strong>, <strong>router</strong>, <strong>SSR</strong>, <strong>SSG</strong>, and other <strong>Frontend solutions</strong>.
    </site-text>
    <img slot="right" src={imgAtom} />
    <site-grid slot="content" columns="1, 2 768px, 3 980px">
        <site-card padding overflow dotColor="var(--site--color-build)">
            <site-text color="subtitle">
                <h4>@atomico/exports</h4>
            </site-text>
            <site-text>
                <small>
                    Automatically generate the exports, types and optimizing the code to distribute with your <strong>package.json</strong>
                </small>
            </site-text>
        </site-card>
        <site-card padding overflow dotColor="var(--site--color-framework)">
            <site-text color="subtitle">
                <h4>@atomico/router</h4>
            </site-text>
            <site-text>
                <small>
                    A router like asynchronous webcomponents really easy to use in SPA applications
                </small>
            </site-text>
        </site-card>
        <site-card padding overflow dotColor="var(--site--color-framework)">
            <site-text color="subtitle">
                <h4>@atomico/store</h4>
            </site-text>
            <site-text>
                <small>
                    Modern state manager, asynchronous and predictable thanks to the use of generators.
                </small>
            </site-text>
        </site-card>
        <site-card padding overflow dotColor="var(--site--color-library)">
            <site-text color="subtitle">
                <h4>@atomico/hooks</h4>
            </site-text>
            <site-text>
                <small>
                    Over 50 highly useful hooks for interface development
                </small>
            </site-text>
        </site-card>
        <site-card padding overflow dotColor="var(--site--color-library)">
            <site-text color="subtitle">
                <h4>@atomico/react</h4>
            </site-text>
            <site-text>
                <small>
                    Super powerful wrapper for <strong>React and Preact (Works with SSR 
                        ðŸ¤¯)</strong>
                </small>
            </site-text>
        </site-card>
        <site-card padding overflow dotColor="var(--site--color-build)">
            <site-text color="subtitle">
                <h4>@atomico/astro</h4>
            </site-text>
            <site-text>
                <small>
                    Create <strong>SSG</strong> and <strong>SSR</strong> sites with Atomico + <a href="https://astro.build/" target="_blank">Astro build</a> as a tool (like this site)
                </small>
            </site-text>
        </site-card>
        <site-card padding overflow dotColor="var(--site--color-build)">
            <site-text color="subtitle">
                <h4>@atomico/vite</h4>
            </site-text>
            <site-text>
                <small>
                    Improves the Atomico development experience + <a href="http://vitejs.dev/" target="_blank">Vite</a> + <a href="https://vitest.dev/" target= "_blank">Vitest</a>
                </small>
            </site-text>
        </site-card>
        <site-card padding overflow dotColor="var(--site--color-library)">
            <site-text color="subtitle">
                <h4>Formilk</h4>
            </site-text>
            <site-text>
                <small>
                    Component system created with Atomico, friendly with Forms and with support for React and Preact
                </small>
            </site-text>
        </site-card>
    </site-grid>
</site-section>